			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">CC is about reducing active mobs fighting or affecting the fight to 1...or to whatever number is acceptable to the group or raid.
<br />

<br />
It doesn't matter how it gets done, wether or not its pretty, or even wether or not SoE intends it...  Results are what matters not semantics.
<br />

<br />
Lull and FD are indeed crowd crontrol, as they reduce the number of the crowd at the inception of aggro.  Pulling is and has always been crowd control, its just one portion of it.
<br />

<br />
Snare is CC, in MPG as a particular example, my SK on a rare example of an add, uses festering, then kites with multiple casts of additional aggro till the 1st mob is dead without issue.  It may not always be pretty, but considering the mod on snare, that he can easily maintain aggro&gt;heals, and that he can move up and down the hate list at will makes it a highly effective method of dealing with the rare add in there.
<br />

<br />
Think about any situation where you bring an enchanter for CC, now for the sake of arguement lets say someone has a chanter nearby C3.  If those mobs are rootable, snareable, lullable, you have another source of haste/slow, and a particular camp can be maintained...would you add an enc to the group or rep their slot for another without charmable mobs present?
<br />

<br />
Shamans had this problem with 30 second fights in GoD.  Other classes had haste, slow was consistenly mitigated to 50 or 75%,  our heals offered too little HPS vs. content, our buffs offered marginal gains, and our sources of damage were too slow considering that 99% of shammies had to actively spend a great deal of time using Cannib 4.  Nothing painted a more grim picture of that early on than pre-nerf Ikkinz.
<br />

<br />
To fully understand the latter bear in mind Cannib 4 has the potential to yeild 85 to 90 mana per tick if a shammie does nothing else and you back out the heal component of that...if a shammie is active 50% of the time then that number drops correspondingly.  When mobs are pulled every 30 seconds and you need to debuff, buff, and spot heal that leaves precious little time for mana regen barring Cannib 5.  Cannib 6 fixes that and reduces time spent to 15 seconds of 61.5 and virtually ensures our mana regen while additionally giving it a nice little boost too <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Enchanters are now in the position we were in, they have been marginalized, especially in some zones and by several classes.  Skilled chanters will still find groups, however slack ass spoiled rotten chanters might find issues locating xp homes~<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=220295" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="color: red">Valkargen MightyPuppy</span></a>
