				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charm is a crowd control tool when used properly. The problem was that there are 2 zones in all of everquest that skew it to a dps tool on the extreme far end, and because it is so extreme in those two zones people take notice.
<br />

<br />
Before oow a charmed pet in a high risk ldon was not dps, it was crowd control. If I had to pull a room with 3 to 5 mobs I would proximity agro then send in pet, because I only had 1 point of agro from proximity the pet would hold all 3 to 5 mobs at bay until I could mez all of them. A charmed pet had the hp and the dps to hold agro, even if I pulled with slow the charmed pet's dps was good enough in high risk ldons to hold the mob off of me. Charmed pets have the hp to crowd control in cases that even a 12 to 14k warrior would have been pasted without heals, and if they recieved heals before the mobs were mezzed the adds would peel off onto the cleric.
<br />

<br />
So yes, charm is a crowd control tool when used properly (if I am correct I believe bards can now charm in tipt/vxed as well). It was due to mob strength that it turned into a dps tool and people cried. I have argued many times that if there was a charmable mob in zone that had the same hp as zone trash and could hold agro as well without the large dps boost it would be perfect for those of us who know how to use charm as a crowd control device.... Now unfortunatly the reduced dps on charmed mobs make it harder for them to hold agro, not to mention when charm breaks the exponentially increased risk just does not make it viable anymore as crowd control tool or a dps tool.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120153" target="_blank" class="postlink">Narith Trumystic
<br />
Spank me baby!</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
