			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I didn't think to ask this, as it just hasnt come up...however with the reduction of DPS of charmed mobs did they alter the modifier or actually alter its given weapon attacks?
<br />

<br />
An example of what I mean is that a warrior with defensive up has a neg 50% modifier to their melee damage, however their weapons values haven't changed.
<br />

<br />
Weapon values, adjusted by damage bonus determines hate generated by swing, haste increases swing rate, and skill caps affect dual attack and dual weild triggers for additional attacks with that same weapon.  That formula modified by proc intervention is what determines melee generated aggro, which can then be base aggro modified by item or spell percentage, ie +aggro from Raex or SK cast etc.
<br />

<br />
If the mob that is charmed has triggered a flag for an alteration of its percentage base modifier then its aggro will remain constant...as aggro is not determined by damage delivered.
<br />

<br />
An example is a warrior generates the same aggro wether defensive or not...only his base damage modifier has been altered, not the hate generated by his attacks.
<br />

<br />
Has anyone tested charms in Omens since the nerf to see if pet aggro has been affected by the changes in dps to determine which was altered, the actual physical attacks corresponding to a weapon number/delay or has it been base modded?<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=220295" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="color: red">Valkargen MightyPuppy</span></a>
<br />
Elder Prophet Fashion Model of <a href="http://pub64.ezboard.com/billuminatis22903" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="color: blue">Illuminatis</span></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
