<br />
Hell the percentages of zones we actually have a pooka pet in is u nder 1% so stop whining <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Before a charmed pet had the dps and hp to hold say 5 mobs at bay, and the dps agro it generated was enough that I could pick each one of the adds off at a time with mez and they would remain on the pet. Due to lowered dps, the agro generated by the pet through dps is aproxamatly 20% of what it was before. This means that unless I give the pet more time to generate agro which I can't do with 5 mobs pounding on it, it will lose agro on the 4 mobs that it is currently not hitting. 
<br />

<br />
I am not exactly sure how it works but lets figure it like this, lets say the mob you are targeting recieves a 1:1 ration on agro done by pet melee, so if pet does 3k in damage then it has 3k agro, mobs that currently are not being beat on also take a percentage of agro which I believe is in proportion to the damage done to other mobs in agro range, lets geuss it at 10%... So if pet does 3k damage to mob a it has 3k agro on mob a, 300 agro on mob b through e.  Now then, spells work the same way as melle in offsetting agro, the spell generates X ammount of agro which is transfered in a percentage to the mobs that assist in agro range, so if I cast mez a 1800 point agro spell I will have 1800 points of agro on the mob I mezzed, and 180 points on each additional mob which is still under the 300 agro the pet has, by the time I cast another mez the pet will have done another 3k in damage generating more agro and therefore keeping my agro under it's allowing me to mez each mob until it is under control.
<br />

<br />
Now then, if that didn't confuse you enough... A charmed mob in oow now does 20% of the dps charmed that it would uncharmed. So now the pet that would have done 3k in damage now does 600 in damage transfering only 60 points of agro to other mobs it has agroed, when I mez I transfer 180 points of agro which is greater than the agro the pet has generated on the adds..... What this means is that if pet is on mob A, and I mez mob B, mobs C through E will now agro me. Mob A will still remain on the pet, but I will have 3 mobs beating on me where before I would have had none.
<br />

<br />
Yet if charm breaks the mob's dps goes back up to normal leaving the same ammount of risk but cutting the reward down to 20% of what it was. Not only do y ou lose the dps the mob could provide but you lose the agro that dps generates.
<br />

<br />
Remember these numbers are not accurate, the percentage of agro generated could be off, but I have always taken it as a given that melee damage agro was 1:1 ratio which I believe that most people will agree on... the percentage transfered to mobs could be any percentage higher than 0 as we know that attacking a mob with it's allies near will agro the allies therfore it does generate agro. Either way you look at it, previously the pet generated enough offset agro to hold mobs at bay in order to be crowd controlled, but now they had thier agro reduced to 20% of what it was making charm almost useless as a crowd control tool.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120153" target="_blank" class="postlink">Narith Trumystic
