<br />
I dont know where you heard this Narith but theres been no change with 10/13 patch</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Was talking to one of the devs and was told it would be added this patch making the trigger effect count as beneficial instead of detrimental which adds 1 point of agro base before removing the 500 agro. It may not have gone in this patch though like many things we are told would but didn't.... What is supposed to happen is a 500 agro reduction should occure without generating any additional agro at all.
<br />

<br />
Ok now Valk.... Like I said before I always took it as damage produced equaled agro on a 1:1 ratio. You are saying that agro is based off the number of swings taken as the very base of it not counting any other modifiers? If this is the case then the agro g enerated was only reduced by 50% because mobs that are charmed go from quadding to doubling therfore reducing the number of swings by 50%.  Even at 50% a mob that would produce say 3000 agro to my 1800 from mez will now produce 1500 to my 1800 from mez making me the target of thier hate yet again and losing the pets ability to work as a crowd control tool. Now then with your formula I am not sure how this would work, many enchanters know that mez is an 1800 point agro producer, a charmed pet used to produce more than this in melee alone in aprox. 5 seconds (2 to 3 seconds between sending the pet in, targeting, and casting mez, and 2.5 second cast time on mez), now however they do not... The fix to this would be to haste the pet increasing the number of swings generated. Unfortunatly this means you go from a pet that charmed does aprox. 100 to 150 dps while unhasted and 500 to 600 unhasted as an uncharmed mob to increasing dps near 70% (70% haste though probably increase of only 50% counting misses) none the less you now are dealing with a pet that low end is doing 750 dps to you, high end is doing 1080 dps to you. That IMHO adds way too much risk to be worth the reward of charm. Wiping your group for the sake of added crowd control is not worth it, unhasted between the dps it adds and the crowd control ability it adds in pre-oow zones the risk is worth it to many enchanters, you lose the crowd control gain along with 80% of the dps in oow and what is the point anymore?
<br />

<br />
What makes this worse is that 3 of the enchanter spells including an ancient spell are charms only useable in oow, any mob prior to oow level 65 and above have been flagged immune making our old charm spells still as useful as before, the new ones only truely useful in oow zones have become worthless due to the mob's reaction to charm.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120153" target="_blank" class="postlink">Narith Trumystic
<br />
Spank me baby!</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
