			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Coming from my experiences of charm killing in Hate with both an enchanter and a Necromancer I would say enchanters have it a lot harder charm soloing then people think.
<br />

<br />
1) No mob in hate will except weapons to make them dual wield so they only double attack.  When you charm this same mob with a necro they automatically dual wield and quad.
<br />

<br />
2)  In order for an enchanter to heal their pets they have to break charm, mez it/root it and then memblur it, their charm costs 700 mana alone on top of the memblur that takes 3 or 4 casts to work.  A necro simply has to FD.  Another fun thing about FDing as a necro is that if the pet is still charmed and you FD, its a complete hate wipe the second you FD.  You can stand right back up if your far enough away and it will not run after you and you won't be on the hate list.
<br />

<br />
3) Enchanters have no way to heal themselves.  If a necro gets down to 10 percent of their life they don't have to gate they can tap themselves back to full pretty easily.  Enchanters also can't just FD and release aggro easy.
<br />

<br />
As a 65 necro with decent gear and AAs, I was able to make an AA about every 20-25 minutes in hate charm killing with almost no chance of dieing and if I died I would be able to rez myself.  The only thing extra that was required was needing a negative MR kit for the pet to make charm breaks not happen as much.  This was with pets that hit for 436 and using the 65 charm, the dps of this pet was around 600ish.  The same enchanter charming the same pet and hasting it would do half the DPS at around 260-290.  They would also have to use 3 times as much mana per kill and per recharm. The only advantage that an Enchanter has over the necro is that they can charm in more zones, but it is still something that requires a lot of skill and a lot of risk for the reward.
<br />

<br />
I am just relating this experience because people who are talking about how overpowered certain things are, really don't understand the whole situation.  Vexed/Tipt certainly aren't gages in how powerful an enchanter are because frankly only 10 percent of this server would have ever been able to get past these trials if it wasn't for these charmed pets.  I think enchanters are pretty boring to play now because the excitement and need isn't there like it was in Seb, you basically sit around and haste and slow and refresh C5 every 100 minutes.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
