				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Hakthek wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I'm curious how you know that Mezz is 1800 hate when the only program(s) able to find the hate on spells that are not pure aggro (like EB, Anger, etc) are against the EULA.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Sk's have pure hate spells...the terror line of spells...so with the help of an SK its pretty easy to figure out the hate generated by almost anything.
<br />

<br />
The 1.2 hate modifier from melee was determined by having an sk proximity aggro a mob, with his back turned to avoid ripostes, chain cast terror till OOM, add up the hate, and parse a warriors melee to determine hate generated per second.  Repeat with a mug in offhand, repeat with mug in mainhand...and so on and so forth.
<br />

<br />
1800 aggro would be assigned to the mez target, however mobs in vicinity would only have spell proximity aggro, and could be pulled from the melee 1 at a time.  Could get dicey against summoners who were swiped by the pet, however against mobs that don't summon could be a useful tool.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=220295" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="color: red">Valkargen MightyPuppy</span></a>
<br />
Elder Prophet Fashion Model of <a href="http://pub64.ezboard.com/billuminatis22903" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="color: blue">Illuminatis</span></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
