And Heyas all, btw )
<br />

<br />
I don't see what the big deal is with chanter nerfing in OoW honestly, and after Narith's 2nd post I stopped caring, too much bloody text to read through. 
<br />
The only class I know cold is the shaman, and I love it to death. I was frustrated with it for awhile, and still am to some degree, because people beg for these lame ass buffs that don't necessarily make a helluva lot of difference. Of course, as the game evolved and they got more powerful, the buffs certainly do help more now than they did when I began playing five years ago.. but seriously, they stick for hours, and the only thing shaman are normally around for is to slow.
<br />
  This is what used to piss me off. Why have a shaman in your group if they can just buff you, and you can go with a bard for the next hour and a half? Or hell, a necromancer if you're hunting undead, or a chanter to charm, haste, and slow? These days, just go with a bloody mage to Malo-line and a beastlord for 65% slow -- lot of dps there.
<br />
  I still don't have an unconditional answer for why one would ever want a shaman, but I stopped looking for one because I realized what I loved about the class was being a utility class. I love the Jack of All Trades roll beyond words, and some of my best memories were of going through some 50k mana an hour keeping useless buffs on level 40 tanks in Blood Inferno raids on the Kael manor and the like, keeping a schedule of who needed to be rebuffed, at what time, and doing the can dance to pump out rediculous amounts of blue stuff.
<br />
  I thought it was pointless, and cried tears of joy when group buffs filled my spellbook ) But I still loved the class for what it was.
<br />

<br />
  These days, I think shaman are a hell of a lot more useful with the improvements to the Cannie and Torpor lines, and the way they are headed.. Unexpected boons, and I enjoy the fact that I make up for 25% of most of my groups' DPS with just the kunark variants, in addition to being there for malo and slow.
<br />
  Oh, and I'm thrilled to death that I can actually solo in Plane of Valor and the Hanging Gardens lol.
<br />

<br />
The only reason why I could see someone leaving chanters because of these changes, is if they didn't truely enjoy their class; and thats a shame ) You should know why you play what you play, and whether you enjoy it by the time you get so far with your character.
<br />

<br />
~Jason, aka 
<br />
Trouvon Aracksus
<br />
65th Shaman of Veeshan, Nemsis
<br />
Eternally of Blood Inferno</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
