			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There's a good reason several MMORPGs require a buffing class to be in a group for the buffs to persist.  I think EQ would probably benefit from this in the long run, but the game would require serious reworking of several spell lists for this to be practical.
<br />

<br />
The first step would be farming out watered-down clarity to non-enchanters -- probably wizards and magicians.  Giving rangers and paladins a watered-down SD-type spell series would also make sense.  Something similar might be looked at for HP buffs, but it isn't like clerics can't find groups, even with Virtue and Temp getting slung all over the place.
<br />

<br />
I also believe that the relative power of a PC vs. mob in EQ is completely out of whack.  The idea of a PC of any class being able to viably solo is something EQ is sorely lacking for many classes.  This probably can't be reasonably changed at this point in the game's development, which is a damned shame.  As I mentioned earlier, if the HP and melee capacity of a mob was a rough match for a PC of equivalent level, charms would be well-balanced.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
