				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Actually Writher from the context of his post he meant to say:
<br />

<br />
"one of those actually is DPS"
<br />

<br />
And even with psuedo mistype, friggin dutchies~, he would still be right.
<br />

<br />
"mobs will do less damage" - check -  Turgurs, balance, cripple and so forth are not dps
<br />

<br />
"PC spells will land better" - check -  Malos, Scent, Tash, and Sinia are not dps.
<br />

<br />
" NPC spells will land less" - check - Resists and ways to avoid incoming spell damage are not dps.
<br />

<br />
"group will regen more mana & hp" - check -  Mana and hp regen speak more to attrition and merely reinforce current roles.
<br />

<br />
DPS classes are defined by their ability to deliver damage in a wide degree of cirmcumstance as a rate higher relatively to others...it is their primary purpose in the group.  Not to enhance DPS delivered but to actually deliver that damage themselves.
<br />

<br />
One of the clues as to wether a class is an DPS enhancer is duplication of effort.  SoT conflicts with SV, Ferocity with AoH, SoV/SoS with Swift, Sinia will overwrite Malos, Turgurs/Balance will overwrite Sha's/Forlorn and that list goes on...  
<br />

<br />
Duplication of effort has diminishing returns for a group and must rely on classes defined as damage dealers as a base to enhance.  Having a group with 1 Ranger, but with a cleric, shaman, enchanter, bard and warrior sans charming will do little DPS...regardless of the dmg enhancing properties of the group...and yet if you viewed enhancing dps as actual dps then that group would tear through mobs.
<br />

<br />
This is again part of the arguement of enchanters.  That the ability to enhance dmg reaches saturation in a group, and without the need for active CC, many classes fulfill that role as well, and bring additional raw damage and competetive forms of enhancement to that same group measured against content.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=220295" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="color: red">Valkargen MightyPuppy</span></a>
