			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Enchanters, Shamans and Bards are the lever classes we're discussing here.  Beastlords also merit some mention.  This means that, depending how you measure it, there are 2-4 in 16 classes in EQ capable of enhancing PC damage, slowing and doing CC.  This ends up being roughly the same ratio as 1 in 6, making one position in a group for CC duty.  Sounds more or less good to me.
<br />

<br />
The worst ratios in EQ are for warriors as plate tanks (in situations where the knight classes are not viable), and at all times clerics and druids as healers (2 in 16 ratio comes out to less than 1 in 6).  This explains why there is a disproportionate number of healers in EQ.  Splitting shaman group roles between CC and heals  is another thing that I view as a huge bone-up on VI's part.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
