			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If they're going to obliterate Charm utility for post-65 Enchanters then they need to give us something to compensate.  Especially since the Lull lines have also been badly reduced.
<br />

<br />
My suggestion is either placing Direcharm bait in OOW zones much like they exist in POP, or a level 70 Animation pet that matches Necro or Mage pets.  Mages still have far more survivability and Mages will still nuke better than we do.  If we're no longer effective for CC, we need to move into more of a DPS role.  And moving our primary DPS sourcing away from Charm towards a useful non-CC Charm or a summoned pet makes sense from a game scalability point of view.
<br />

<br />
We also need an upgrade to the Tash line of spells.  It's been since Luclin.  Same with our slows.
<br />

<br />
Frankly, C6 does not give us a group role.  You can beg C3 in PoKnowledge and hunt for an entire afternoon.  Haste gives us a MARGINAL group role, but with the haste cap, Shamans, Beastlords, and Bards all having Haste as well, it's just not a compelling reason to pick an Enchanter.
<br />

<br />
I HATE charmsoloing.  It's boring, and it's RVR simply isn't worthwhile, of course I only have a single EQ account.  Having a pocket Cleric might well alter that.  I prefer to group.
<br />

<br />
And what's really irritating is that even in groups, until I get the higher-level lulls and Mez rune handins, I am forced to play the boring, lazy type of Enchanter I really detest.  I like to pull.  I enjoy peeling apart clustered spawns.  I like racking and stacking mobs in a neat line for the party to kill.  And LoY was the last expansion I could do that in.
<br />

<br />
Right now the only thing Charm is good for is killing placeholders when farming.  Charm the PH, watch its neighbors aggro it, watch it die from its' pathetic reduced DPS, and gate out as it falls over.  Then log to your necro when you get the named to spawn.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
